"title": "5171: nose",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5171: nose",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>The nose as part of the human body</h2>\n<h3>Human life is given and sustained through the nostrils</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:7\">GEN 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:22\">GEN 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:20\">NUM 11:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:3\">JOB 27:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:22\">ISA 2:22</a></p>\n<h3>The nose and the sense of smell</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:27\">GEN 27:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:25\">JOB 39:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:11\">SNG 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:27\">DAN 3:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:10\">AMO 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:17\">1CO 12:17</a></p>\n<h2>Animals snort and sniff through their noses</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:20\">JOB 39:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:18\">JOB 41:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:20\">JOB 41:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:24\">JER 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:16\">JER 8:16</a></p>\n<h2>The nose and sneezing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:35\">2KI 4:35</a></p>\n<h2>The nose as an object of beauty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:4\">SNG 7:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The nose may be adorned with rings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:12\">EZK 16:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:22\">GEN 24:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:30\">GEN 24:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:47\">GEN 24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:21\">ISA 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>The nose is vulnerable to attack</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:33\">PRO 30:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:25\">EZK 23:25</a></p>\n<h2>Captives are led by rings or hooks in the nose</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:28\">2KI 19:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:29\">ISA 37:29</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:11\">2CH 33:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:2\">AMO 4:2</a></p>\n<h2>Contempt is communicated by means of the nose</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:5\">PSA 10:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:4\">ISA 57:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:13\">MAL 1:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:14\">LUK 16:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:35\">LUK 23:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:32\">ACT 17:32</a></p>\n<h2>Offence is taken, metaphorically, by the nose</h2>\n<h3>People take offence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:21\">2SA 16:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:30\">GEN 34:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:21\">EXO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:6\">2SA 10:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:6\">1CH 19:6</a></p>\n<h3>God takes offence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:5\">ISA 65:5</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God's power is indicated by the blast of his nostrils</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:8\">EXO 15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:9\">2SA 22:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:8\">PSA 18:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:16\">2SA 22:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:15\">PSA 18:15</a></p>\n<h2>Lifeless idols have noses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:6\">PSA 115:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:28\">DEU 4:28</a></p>",
